Job Description:
Data Scientist Co-Op




Your Tasks and Responsibilities

Independently develop algorithms in R and/or Python to clean, process, analyze and visualize large multivariate datasets (genotypic, environmental, and phenotypic);
Work closely with data science team and business partners to break down complex business problems to build feasible solutions that are impactful, accurate and validated;
Design and prototype models using machine learning, statistical modeling, process modeling, and other techniques such as machine learning;
Work with mentor and other researchers and scientists to quickly gain domain knowledge and understand business processes;
Present data driven insight, recommendations, and solutions to a broad range of audiences including peers, leadership and internal customers in a clear, interpretable manner;
Expand professional networks with the business and the Data and Data Science Community

Required Qualifications

Pursuing Ph.D. (or M.S. final year) in a discipline related to Data Science (e.g., Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science/Engineering);
Theoretical knowledge and practical experience with advanced statistical and machine learning modeling techniques;
Strong desire to develop a career in Data Science;
Fluency in using SQL, Python or R for data manipulation, computational statistics, and model development;
Knowledge and experience in modeling environmental and crop phenology data;
Strong communication skills and the ability to work with diverse cross-functional teams;
Ability to turn complex biological or engineering data into meaningful insights;
Execute responsibilities with knowledge, integrity, commitment, and excellence

Preferred Qualifications

Experience with mixed effects regression, clustering, outlier detection, survival analysis modeling
Technical experience working with Github, Google BigQuery, and Markdown Terms
Project Duration: at least six months
Expectation: 40 hrs/week

